32:55.240 --> 32:58.376
So, Sharks,
who wants to roll with me

32:58.376 --> 33:00.879
to "tape" the world by storm?

33:00.879 --> 33:03.448
Wow.
Well, great, great demo.

33:03.448 --> 33:04.449
-Good presentation.
-Great presentation.

33:04.449 --> 33:05.851
Thank you.
So in front of you guys,

33:05.851 --> 33:07.719
you'll see a sample

33:07.719 --> 33:09.354
of our eight-pack
of athletic tape.

33:09.354 --> 33:11.556
It's one of our best sellers.

33:11.556 --> 33:14.893
So we sell all sports tapes.
That is all that we sell.

33:14.893 --> 33:18.196
And we actually do
pretty, pretty well, I think.

33:18.196 --> 33:20.298
I bet with those numbers
you tossed out,

33:20.298 --> 33:21.633
I bet you're doing very well.
Greiner: Yeah, right?

33:21.633 --> 33:23.768
Oh, the numbers?
Yeah, the numbers.

33:23.768 --> 33:27.405
Sales --
about $24,000 in sales.

33:27.405 --> 33:28.773
-What?
-That's it?

33:28.773 --> 33:29.941
-What?
-Yesterday.

33:29.941 --> 33:31.643
-Yesterday.
-Yesterday.

33:31.643 --> 33:33.044
All right, you got us.
You got us.

33:33.044 --> 33:35.780
So lifetime, we've sold
about $12.2 million of tape.

33:35.780 --> 33:37.682
-What?!
-Whoa! Whoa!

33:37.682 --> 33:40.819
And I say "we," I mean me.
I'm a one-man show.

33:40.819 --> 33:41.920
-Is that --
-You are?

33:41.920 --> 33:43.788
Is that one year's
worth of sales?

33:43.788 --> 33:45.657
One year -- this year,
year to date, $5 million.

33:45.657 --> 33:46.791
-What?!
-Come on!

33:46.791 --> 33:48.059
-$5 million year to date?
-Yeah.

33:48.059 --> 33:49.761
What distributor
are you using?

33:49.761 --> 33:51.463
So we sell primarily
through Amazon.

33:51.463 --> 33:52.931
So tell us
how you got there,

33:52.931 --> 33:54.799
because that's your
magic sauce, right?
Yeah, yeah.

33:54.799 --> 33:57.536
Yeah, like, $5 million
is unbelievable.

33:57.536 --> 33:58.670
Thank you.

33:58.670 --> 34:00.672
This year, we'll close out
$6.2 million,

34:00.672 --> 34:01.873
$6.5 million,
somewhere in there.

34:01.873 --> 34:03.441
What are you gonna make
on the $6.2 million?

34:03.441 --> 34:05.677
About 20%.

34:05.677 --> 34:08.113
Ah! So therein
lies the rub, right?
Greiner: Yeah.

34:08.113 --> 34:10.282
Because these should have
a lot of margin.

34:10.282 --> 34:13.318
So ad spend, right?
That's there.

34:13.318 --> 34:16.721
About 20% of our margin
is in ads.

34:16.721 --> 34:18.623
So you said you're gonna do
$6 million to $7 million.

34:18.623 --> 34:21.760
So when you say 20%, is that
your pretax net earnings?

34:21.760 --> 34:24.229
-Yeah. So that's EBITDA.
-Okay.

34:24.229 --> 34:27.232
All of that goes
right back into inventory.

34:27.232 --> 34:29.067
And so therein lies
the problem, right?

34:29.067 --> 34:31.202
Right.
It's a beast that
you're constantly feeding.

34:31.202 --> 34:33.104
But, Seneca, the big-tape people
can do the same thing.

34:33.104 --> 34:34.673
Like, what's making yours
stand out?

34:34.673 --> 34:37.876
Some of this tape that you use,
right, people are allergic.

34:37.876 --> 34:40.111
And they'll have rashes
or pull their hair out.
Greiner: Right.

34:40.111 --> 34:42.347
So there's a different adhesive
that we actually have

34:42.347 --> 34:43.448
in our tape.

34:43.448 --> 34:44.849
It's not proprietary,

34:44.849 --> 34:46.751
but no one's used it
in the way that we're using it.

34:46.751 --> 34:48.787
So that's
the secret sauce?
That's it. Yeah.

34:48.787 --> 34:50.322
So there's no patent
on your product at all?

34:50.322 --> 34:51.523
No, there's no patent.

34:51.523 --> 34:53.058
Cuban:
It takes a lot of learning

34:53.058 --> 34:55.393
in the advertising
and SEO space.

34:55.393 --> 34:57.696
Yeah.
So what was the process
you went through there

34:57.696 --> 34:58.897
to get to the top?
Let me answer that.

34:58.897 --> 35:01.132
About seven years ago,

35:01.132 --> 35:04.069
